('D-006', 'F-2023-005', 'covenant_compliance_certificate',
 'Q4 2024 Covenant Compliance Certificate: Pinnacle Logistics Group',
 'COVENANT COMPLIANCE CERTIFICATE\n\nDate: January 30, 2025\nBorrower: Pinnacle Logistics Group\nFacility: $12M Asset-Based Revolving Line (F-2023-005)\nReporting Period: Q4 2024 (October 1 - December 31, 2024)\n\nThe undersigned hereby certifies the following covenant calculations:\n\n1. MAXIMUM LEVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not to exceed 3.00x\n   Actual: 4.10x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 1.10x over limit\n\n2. MINIMUM INTEREST COVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not less than 1.75x\n   Actual: 1.30x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 0.45x below requirement\n\n3. MINIMUM EBITDA (Trailing 12 months)\n   Covenant Requirement: Not less than $6,000,000\n   Actual: $5,200,000\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: $800,000 below requirement\n\nNOTES:\nThe deterioration in financial metrics is attributable to (i) higher-than-expected fuel costs in Q4 due to supply disruptions, (ii) loss of two mid-size customer contracts representing approximately $4M in annual revenue, and (iii) continued integration costs related to the Delta Transport acquisition.\n\nManagement is implementing a cost reduction plan targeting $2M in annual savings through route optimization and fleet right-sizing. The company has also engaged an investment bank to explore strategic alternatives including a potential minority equity investment.\n\nThe Borrower acknowledges the covenant violations and requests a 90-day forbearance period to execute the restructuring plan.',
 'Robert Kim, CFO - Pinnacle Logistics Group', '2025-01-30'),

('D-007', 'F-2023-003', 'covenant_compliance_certificate',
 'Q4 2024 Covenant Compliance Certificate: Meridian Health Systems',
 'COVENANT COMPLIANCE CERTIFICATE\n\nDate: January 25, 2025\nBorrower: Meridian Health Systems\nFacility: $20M Working Capital Revolver (F-2023-003)\nReporting Period: Q4 2024 (October 1 - December 31, 2024)\n\nThe undersigned hereby certifies the following covenant calculations:\n\n1. MAXIMUM LEVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not to exceed 4.00x\n   Actual: 2.30x\n   Status: IN COMPLIANCE\n   Headroom: 1.70x\n\n2. MINIMUM FIXED CHARGE COVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not less than 1.25x\n   Actual: 1.95x\n   Status: IN COMPLIANCE\n   Headroom: 0.70x\n\nNOTES:\nMeridian Health Systems continues to demonstrate strong financial performance driven by expansion of outpatient surgery centers and growth in telehealth services. Revenue increased 15% year-over-year while EBITDA margins expanded 200 basis points to 15.0%. The company completed the opening of two new ambulatory surgery centers in Q4 which are expected to contribute $8M in incremental annual revenue once fully ramped.\n\nAll financial covenants are in compliance with substantial headroom. Management projects continued improvement in leverage metrics as new facilities ramp to full utilization.',
 'Lisa Park, VP Finance - Meridian Health Systems', '2025-01-25'),

('D-008', 'F-2023-009', 'covenant_compliance_certificate',
 'Q4 2024 Covenant Compliance Certificate: Cascade Paper & Packaging',
 'COVENANT COMPLIANCE CERTIFICATE\n\nDate: February 5, 2025\nBorrower: Cascade Paper & Packaging\nFacility: $8M Asset-Based Revolving Line (F-2023-009)\nReporting Period: Q4 2024 (October 1 - December 31, 2024)\n\nThe undersigned hereby certifies the following covenant calculations:\n\n1. MAXIMUM LEVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not to exceed 3.00x\n   Actual: 4.20x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 1.20x over limit\n\n2. MINIMUM FIXED CHARGE COVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not less than 1.10x\n   Actual: 0.82x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 0.28x below requirement\n\n3. MAXIMUM CAPITAL EXPENDITURES\n   Covenant Requirement: Not to exceed $2,000,000 per fiscal year\n   Actual: $2,400,000\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: $400,000 over limit\n\nNOTES:\nThe company experienced significant margin compression in Q4 due to elevated input costs (recycled fiber prices increased 22% year-over-year) combined with competitive pricing pressure from larger integrated producers. The capex overrun relates to emergency replacement of a corrugating machine that failed in November.\n\nManagement has retained a restructuring advisor and is evaluating options including (i) sale of the company\'s Portland distribution facility, (ii) renegotiation of supply contracts, and (iii) workforce reduction targeting 15% of salaried positions. The borrower is requesting a comprehensive covenant amendment package.',
 'Thomas Grant, Controller - Cascade Paper & Packaging', '2025-02-05'),

('D-009', 'F-2022-024', 'covenant_compliance_certificate',
 'Q3 2024 Covenant Compliance Certificate: Keystone Auto Parts LLC',
 'COVENANT COMPLIANCE CERTIFICATE\n\nDate: October 28, 2024\nBorrower: Keystone Auto Parts LLC\nFacility: $7M Asset-Based Revolving Line (F-2022-024)\nReporting Period: Q3 2024 (July 1 - September 30, 2024)\n\nThe undersigned hereby certifies the following covenant calculations:\n\n1. MAXIMUM LEVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not to exceed 3.00x\n   Actual: 5.80x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 2.80x over limit\n\n2. MINIMUM FIXED CHARGE COVERAGE RATIO\n   Covenant Requirement: Not less than 1.10x\n   Actual: 0.55x\n   Status: NOT IN COMPLIANCE\n   Variance: 0.55x below requirement\n\nNOTES:\nKeystone Auto Parts continues to experience severe financial deterioration driven by the industry-wide shift from internal combustion engine parts to EV components. Revenue declined 25% year-over-year as legacy OEM customers reduced orders. The company\'s Detroit and Toledo facilities are operating at 40% capacity utilization.\n\nThe borrower has engaged legal counsel regarding potential options including an orderly wind-down, asset sale, or restructuring under Chapter 11 protection. The lender should expect a formal forbearance and workout proposal within 30 days.\n\nThe company acknowledges that continued operations may not be viable without significant capital infusion or strategic transaction.',
 'David Chen, CFO - Keystone Auto Parts LLC', '2024-10-28'),

