('D-010', 'F-2024-008', 'collateral_appraisal',
 'Collateral Appraisal: Ironbridge Energy - Permian Basin Compression Complex',
 'INDEPENDENT APPRAISAL REPORT\n\nProperty: Permian Basin Pipeline Compression Station Complex\nClient: Specialty Finance Direct Lending Group\nEffective Date: May 1, 2024\nPrepared by: Western Valuation Associates, LLC\n\nPROPERTY DESCRIPTION:\nThe subject property consists of four natural gas compression stations located along a 45-mile pipeline corridor in Midland County, Texas. The stations were constructed between 2015 and 2019 and contain a total of 12 compression units with aggregate capacity of 180 MMcf/d.\n\nVALUATION SUMMARY:\n- Cost Approach (Replacement Cost Less Depreciation): $38,200,000\n- Income Approach (Discounted Cash Flow): $34,800,000\n- Sales Comparison Approach: $33,300,000\n\nFINAL RECONCILED VALUE: $33,300,000\n\nThe reconciled value weights the sales comparison approach most heavily given three comparable transactions within the past 18 months. The income approach supports the conclusion but carries uncertainty around contract renewal assumptions. The cost approach is presented for reference but given limited weight due to functional obsolescence considerations.\n\nKEY ASSUMPTIONS:\n- Existing take-or-pay contracts remain in force through their stated terms\n- No material environmental liabilities beyond known conditions\n- Compression equipment maintains current operating efficiency with standard maintenance\n\nLIMITING CONDITIONS:\nThis appraisal is subject to the extraordinary assumptions and limiting conditions detailed in the addendum. The appraiser has not conducted environmental assessments. Value conclusion assumes continued access to pipeline right-of-way easements.',
 'Western Valuation Associates, LLC', '2024-05-01'),

('D-011', 'F-2024-025', 'collateral_appraisal',
 'Collateral Appraisal: Bridgewater Real Estate - NJ Office Portfolio',
 'INDEPENDENT APPRAISAL REPORT\n\nProperty: Northern New Jersey Office Portfolio (3 Buildings)\nClient: Specialty Finance Direct Lending Group\nEffective Date: March 15, 2024\nPrepared by: Cushman & Partners Valuation Group\n\nPROPERTY DESCRIPTION:\nThe subject portfolio consists of three Class B office buildings totaling 285,000 rentable square feet located in Parsippany and Morris Plains, New Jersey. The buildings were constructed between 1985 and 1995 and last renovated in 2010-2012.\n\nCURRENT OCCUPANCY: 62% (weighted average across portfolio)\nIN-PLACE NOI: $2,850,000 per annum\n\nVALUATION SUMMARY:\n- As-Is Value (Current Condition and Occupancy): $40,000,000 ($140/SF)\n- As-Stabilized Value (90% Occupancy, Post-Renovation): $52,000,000 ($182/SF)\n\nThe as-is value reflects current market conditions including elevated suburban office vacancy rates of 18% in the Morris County submarket. The as-stabilized value assumes successful execution of the flex/hybrid workspace repositioning strategy with $8M in capital improvements over 18 months.\n\nMARKET OBSERVATIONS:\nThe Northern New Jersey suburban office market has experienced bifurcation between renovated, amenity-rich properties and older commodity product. Properties that have undergone modernization are achieving rents 25-35% above unrenovated peers. The flex workspace conversion thesis is supported by leasing velocity at comparable repositioned assets in the submarket.',
 'Cushman & Partners Valuation Group', '2024-03-15'),

