('D-012', 'F-2024-002', 'amendment_letter',
 'First Amendment to Credit Agreement: Apex Manufacturing Corp',
 'FIRST AMENDMENT TO CREDIT AGREEMENT\n\nDate: January 15, 2025\n\nThis First Amendment (this "Amendment") amends the Credit Agreement dated January 15, 2024 (the "Credit Agreement") between Apex Manufacturing Corp ("Borrower") and the Lender.\n\nRECITALS:\nWHEREAS, the Borrower has notified the Lender that it expects to breach the Maximum Leverage Ratio covenant for the fiscal quarter ending December 31, 2024;\n\nWHEREAS, the Borrower has requested a temporary increase in the Maximum Leverage Ratio covenant level and the Lender is willing to grant such modification subject to the terms herein;\n\nAMENDMENTS:\n1. Section 7.1(a) - Maximum Leverage Ratio is hereby amended as follows:\n   - For the fiscal quarter ending December 31, 2024: increased from 3.50x to 4.00x\n   - For the fiscal quarter ending March 31, 2025: increased from 3.50x to 3.75x\n   - All subsequent periods: reverts to 3.50x\n\n2. Amendment Fee: Borrower shall pay a one-time amendment fee of 25 basis points on the outstanding principal balance ($21,250).\n\n3. Additional Reporting: During the amendment period, Borrower shall provide monthly (rather than quarterly) financial statements and management commentary.\n\n4. Pricing Adjustment: The applicable interest rate margin shall increase by 50 basis points during any period in which the Leverage Ratio exceeds 3.50x.\n\nAll other terms and conditions of the Credit Agreement remain in full force and effect.',
 'Legal Department', '2025-01-15'),

('D-013', 'F-2023-005', 'amendment_letter',
 'Second Amendment and Limited Waiver: Pinnacle Logistics Group',
 'SECOND AMENDMENT AND LIMITED WAIVER TO CREDIT AGREEMENT\n\nDate: October 15, 2024\n\nThis Second Amendment and Limited Waiver amends the Credit Agreement dated September 1, 2023 between Pinnacle Logistics Group ("Borrower") and the Lender.\n\nWAIVER:\nThe Lender hereby waives the Events of Default arising from the Borrower\'s failure to comply with (i) the Maximum Leverage Ratio covenant and (ii) the Minimum Interest Coverage Ratio covenant for the fiscal quarter ending September 30, 2024. This waiver is limited solely to the specified defaults for the specified testing period.\n\nAMENDMENTS:\n1. Maximum Leverage Ratio: Temporarily increased from 3.00x to 3.50x for Q3 2024 and Q4 2024 testing periods. Reverts to 3.00x for Q1 2025 and subsequent periods.\n\n2. Minimum Interest Coverage: Temporarily decreased from 1.75x to 1.50x for Q3 2024 and Q4 2024 testing periods.\n\n3. Advance Rate Reduction: Maximum advance rate on eligible receivables reduced from 80% to 75% effective immediately.\n\n4. Cash Dominion: Full cash dominion activated. All collections must flow through the lender-controlled lockbox.\n\n5. Management Reporting: Weekly cash flow projections required through March 31, 2025.\n\n6. Waiver Fee: $120,000 (1.0% of commitment), payable upon execution.\n\nCONDITIONS PRECEDENT:\n- Borrower must deliver a board-approved business plan by November 15, 2024\n- Retention of financial advisor acceptable to Lender\n- No additional indebtedness without prior written consent',
 'Legal Department', '2024-10-15'),

